article.headline: Maine 72, Albany, N.Y. 61
article.story: ORONO, Maine -- Kaimondre Owes scored 20 points off the bench and Sean McNally added 14 and six rebounds as Maine won for only the second time in nine games by beating Albany, N.Y., 72-61, on Saturday. Maine (7-11, 2-3 America East Conference) was ahead 32-24 early in the second half and pulled away with seven straight points. Gerald McLemore hit a jumper, Malachi Peay -- who had 11 points -- followed with a 3-point play and McNally converted an offensive rebound. The margin later reached 52-29. The Great Danes (11-7, 3-20) could get no closer than 60-50 with 4:18 left. Will Harris had 20 points, Brian Connelly had 13 points and nine rebounds and Tim Ambrose 10 points for Albany, which had won three straight and was in first place in the conference. Trailing 17-16, Maine took the lead for good with 10 straight points, including two 3-pointers by Owes.
